flowRoot.flowPara: Gent Matberg, a 15-year old boy from the downtown New York who wants to be a real musician and be famous around the globe. He always wanted to own a drum machine but the ones in the market are either very expensive or very toy-like. He wanted a drum machine which should be affordable and with decent features to dive into his music career.

It should be able to replicate some common drum patterns and instruments that would be needed to to pursue his music life. The goal is to have a portable drum machine that could be used for production and live performances. This way Ghent could get started in music production.

The product can be used anywhere you wish, like on a desk or even could be held in your hand in a studio or even on a stage. The customer will obtain information on the product via the pitch we made - user video , brochure and the website. Having the online presence makes it easier to be found by the intended customers by using targeted ads. The decision can be influenced by the reviews about our product online, our online marketing, and by friends who have heard about our product. We would see our product direct to the customer to cut out the middle man and give Ghent the best value possible.

Current products are expensive and lack the flexability in sound output that our products aims to give. Some current products are also confusing to use and setup - failing to work as expected. Ghent is thrifty so he is worried about wasting money on a bad product.

Current products are what would allow him to make music so that makes him happy even though they are not ideal by any means. Current products support industry standards like MIDI which would allow him to hook up other instruments to drum machines in the future - this prevents vendor lock-in and makes things more extensible.
